				<outline text="string.markdownProcess" created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:33:16 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/?verb=string.markdownProcess&quot;&gt;DocServer page&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:33:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I'm interested in processing Markdown in Drummer:" created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:33:44 GMT" flNumberedSubs="true">
						<outline text="Reading outline files that are encoded in Markdown, which is popular in Obsidian and LogSeq. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:46:23 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Generating output from the outliner using Markdown syntax. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:46:28 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="I haven't yet figured out how to do either of these, thinking about it -- looking for ideas. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:46:33 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In the meantime I thought it would be a good idea to get easy Markdown support into the language, see what happens. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:47:31 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I started a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerRFC/issues/4&quot;&gt;thread&lt;/a&gt; for discussion. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 14:35:02 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="If you have a project to share.." created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 16:56:42 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="The way to go about it is to post an item to on the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerrfc/issues&quot;&gt;RFC issues&lt;/a&gt; page. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 16:56:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If people want to see it, they will. The other option, spamming other people's messages is exactly what we don't want. It's the equivalent of the rule at BloggerCon where people weren't allowed to talk about their own products unless invited to by the discussion leader. In this case the DL is the person who started the RFC. It's not okay to volunteer a pointer to your project in response to an RFC. You could politely and humbly send an email. But please don't overdo it. Spam is spam and no likes it. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 16:57:03 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This has to be a hard line, because if it's not, if this product is able to grow, it will eventually devolve into something like Twitter where almost everyone all the time is trying to be heard. Nothing wrong with that, I love Twitter, but that won't work for a collegial developer community, as the one this is and will stay. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 16:58:23 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You must know that I've been through it all. I'm not particularly open-minded about this stuff. I love it when people put out their ideas, and it gives us away to connect with other products, or other users, or help each other have a more powerful environment to use. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 16:59:27 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Please don't call your work &quot;Drummer&quot;" created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 18:04:01 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I chose a unique name for this product. It's not descriptive.  " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 18:04:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="When you call your product Drummer -- that's not fair. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 18:04:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Be creative. If your work requires a product name, pick one yourself. " created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 18:04:29 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Thanks." created="Tue, 02 Nov 2021 18:04:48 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="November 1" created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 14:15:08 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="01">
				<outline text="freeDiskSpace" created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 15:27:27 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Not related to Drummer specifically, I had to update my &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/freeDiskSpace&quot;&gt;freeDiskSpace&lt;/a&gt; Node package and app because there was a breaking change (undocumented apparently) in a package called &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-cmd&quot;&gt;node-cmd&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 15:27:30 GMT" isComment="false" image="http://scripting.com/images/2017/12/06/bizarroSuperman.png"/>
					<outline text="The problem was fixed by figuring out which was the last version of node-cmd that worked, and editing my &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/freeDiskSpace/blob/master/package.json#L12&quot;&gt;dependencies list&lt;/a&gt; to make sure that was the version we used. The routine that disappeared was the central routine, basically the only thing the package actually did. " created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 15:31:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Is this a way to run a platform? " created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 15:32:03 GMT"/>
					<outline text="As usual this change came up when I was provisioning a new server, when I was already juggling lots of other details, as if I needed to go rewrite a package of my own that I have allocated zero percent of my consciousness to. :smile:" created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 15:30:18 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The monthly ritual is complete" created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 14:15:09 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I carefully &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/11/01/125625.html?title=theMonthlyRitual&quot;&gt;documented&lt;/a&gt; the monthly ritual this month because it's the first time I did it since Drummer shipped." created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 14:15:13 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There was a bug. The first time I built the Scripting News home page after deleting the October branch, the month of October was a jumble of days in October, whcih now that I found and fixed the problem make sense. " created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 14:15:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It was a matter of calling the JavaScript function getDay when I meant to call getDate. Otherwise even though the new code that was untested until today, it seems to be correct. The home page of my blog is good, even though the content for October is coming from the cache Old School keeps, not from my outline. " created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 14:16:33 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If you want to try it, you can -- but be sure you have a backup! I was glad I had mine. " created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 14:17:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/2021/10/30/145939.html?title=oldSchoolDustsweeping#a150136&quot;&gt;advisory&lt;/a&gt; I posted on the 30th." created="Mon, 01 Nov 2021 14:18:31 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="October 2021" created="Fri, 01 Oct 2021 14:47:15 GMT" name="october2021" type="calendarMonth">
			<outline text="October 31" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 13:47:21 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="31">
				<outline text="Drummer &amp; Gatsby via Papascott" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 13:47:22 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="An &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerRFC/issues/3&quot;&gt;announcement&lt;/a&gt; from Scott Hanson that he has Drummer working with Gatsby. " created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 13:47:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.papascott.de/archives/2021/10/31/blogging-in-gatsby-with-drummer/&quot;&gt;post&lt;/a&gt; that is the proof of concept. " created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 13:48:05 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Apparently the software is a Gatsby plugin. " created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 14:07:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Gatsby is an &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby&quot;&gt;open source&lt;/a&gt; static site generator. It's &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/gatsby-e828&quot;&gt;also&lt;/a&gt; a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gatsbyjs.com/about/&quot;&gt;company&lt;/a&gt;. Based in Berkeley, has raised $46.8 million." created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 13:49:35 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Looking for an easy tutorial. I have literally never used it, so i would like to at least be able to talk about it, explain what it is and what this connection means. " created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 13:52:39 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Glad to have it! Our goal is to connect everything with everything. Outlines in the middle. We rock! ðŸ˜€" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2021 13:53:06 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 30" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 14:59:38 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="30">
				<outline text="Thesaurus" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:42:46 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Drummer has a thesaurus. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:42:49 GMT"/>
					<outline text="A &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0AId6zUZYko&quot;&gt;video demo&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:42:56 GMT" urlvideo="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0AId6zUZYko"/>
					<outline text="How to" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:43:28 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
						<outline text="First, do a hard-reload of Drummer to get updates." created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:44:39 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Create a new headline" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:44:36 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Set the type to word."/>
						<outline text="Enter a word in the headline."/>
						<outline text="Double-click."/>
						<outline text="A list of synonyms fills in under the headline."/>
						<outline text="You can then double-click on any of them."/>
						<outline text="Think of it as navigating the thesaurus in an outline."/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Bookmarks demo" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:41:34 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I came across a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u4pN9L2ArGs&quot;&gt;video demo&lt;/a&gt; I did of Bookmarks on September 4, before most people were in the loop on Drummer. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:41:38 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Posts must have type attributes" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:04:50 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="In the confusion of last week's fixes for date stuff, a new rule was introduced that has caused some concern in the blogs and in the support forum. The rule comes in two forms:" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:08:41 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
						<outline text="Use the big + icon to create new posts. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:09:31 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Every post must have a type attribute that's either outline, link or tweet. There may be others as we go. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:09:40 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="I am sorry for the breakage this has caused. I am a strong advocate of the No Breakage School of software development. But this is early days for Drummer, and not making this a rule from the outset was a mistake I didn't want to live with going forward. The CMS must have a way of telling that something is a post, and only going by the calendar structure isn't something I want to depend on." created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:10:05 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If this is a big problem, we can address it with a script that goes through your outline and finds all subs of days that don;'t have type attributes and put them there. It would not be a hard script to write, and I would be happy to do it, if it's needed. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:11:45 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I've started a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/103&quot;&gt;thread&lt;/a&gt; on the support forum for this topic, also for any problems resulting from the big shakeup of this week. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:12:46 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Still diggin!&lt;/i&gt; is still the thing we do. :boom:" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:13:16 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Old School dust-sweeping" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 14:59:39 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="This doesn't concern Drummer users directly, but I thought it deserved a change note." created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 14:59:55 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I installed the new version of Old School on the server that builds Scripting News. This predates Drummer by 4.5 years, so it works somewhat differently. It seems to work, I did a bunch of writing and rebuilding this morning. I made a couple of changes in cosmetic areas. The result is &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/30.html&quot;&gt;something&lt;/a&gt; that looks exactly like it should as far as I can tell. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:00:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In a change note on the 28th, I &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/2021/10/28/212107.html?title=thisChangeWasDisruptive#a212312&quot;&gt;talked&lt;/a&gt; about how you can delete days off the end of your outline, how this is a necessary feature for Scripting News, where I have been writing in the same OPML file for 4.5 years. It would have become unwieldy long before. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:01:36 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's my suggestion for Drummer users considering using this feature, and I think eventually most of you &lt;i&gt;will&lt;/i&gt; want to use it. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:02:29 GMT">
						<outline text="Wait until November 1 or 2, after I give the all-clear, when we see if it works on Scripting News, and after I've had a chance to fix any resulting problems. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:02:54 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="I'd rather be the test case on this myself before trying to figure out why something went wrong on one of your systems. " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:03:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This is new code, and it's better to assume it has problems than just assuming it works as documented. Remember Murphy's Law and It's even worse than it appears.  " created="Sat, 30 Oct 2021 15:03:46 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 29" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:19:32 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="29">
				<outline text="DrummerCms changes" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:19:33 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Link nodes now work properly. " created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:21:09 GMT">
						<outline text="Here's a &lt;a href=&quot;http://clueless.lucky.wtf/2021/10/30.html#a131838&quot;&gt;demo&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:21:33 GMT"/>
						<outline text="They were lost temporarily in the big shakeup." created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:23:19 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Fixed a bug where an empty blog would cause server to stop responding." created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:13:54 GMT">
						<outline text="By empty blog --&gt; no calendar, no typed headlines of type outline, tweet or link." created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:19:54 GMT"/>
						<outline text="An empty blog &lt;a href=&quot;http://oldschool.scripting.com/hsy/&quot;&gt;looks&lt;/a&gt; kind of stark. I had never seen one before." created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:20:23 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 28" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:19:35 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="28">
				<outline text="And thanks!" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 01:59:46 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="For all the help. " created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 01:59:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In all my years making software and working with users, I've never worked with so great a group of people. Amazing. I know I've said it before but I continue to be impressed! :-)" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 01:59:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I said in a comment today -- developers need support too. " created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 02:00:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And for that I am grateful." created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 02:00:55 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="We won't do it this way again" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 01:57:55 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I can't remember the last time a product I made had such a chaotic transition. " created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 01:58:00 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The first order of business is to stabilize everything, so we're not dealing with broken blogs or outlines. " created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 01:58:14 GMT"/>
					<outline text="That's where my focus will be, but at the same time I want to release new stuff too. " created="Fri, 29 Oct 2021 01:58:38 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="This change was disruptive" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 21:21:07 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Three things changed re blogs in today's Old School changes." created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 21:21:12 GMT" flNumberedSubs="true">
						<outline text="When rendering a blog, an outline must have one of three types. outline, tweet, link. We may add other types, but headlines must have a &lt;i&gt;type&lt;/i&gt; attribute with one of these values to be a blog post. " created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 21:21:28 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Every headline should have a &lt;i&gt;created&lt;/i&gt; attribute. That value and the value of the &lt;i&gt;timeZoneOffset&lt;/i&gt; head-level attribute are what we key on to know which day &quot;bucket&quot; a post belongs in." created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 21:25:50 GMT"/>
						<outline text="You can delete days of posts at the end of your outline without them disappearing from your blog. This is an essential feature for a blog like Scripting News, that has been in the same OPML file for 4.5 years. I have to be able to remove stuff. I actually completely clear my outline at the beginning of every month after archiving it in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/Scripting-News/tree/master/blog&quot;&gt;Scripting-News repo&lt;/a&gt;." created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 21:23:12 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Use the big plus icon to create new posts and everything will work well. You can add the the attributes by hand, and I can't imagine why you'd want to do that. Of course you can add and change atts with scripts. :smile:" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 21:25:22 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The main CMS server is now updated" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:57:35 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="And is running the new code." created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:57:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="So if you rebuild your blog using the Build My Blog command in the Tools menu, it should work as if it were being built in Experiment 3, except it will be at the real address of your blog. " created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:57:47 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Hopefully it will operate smoothly. Fingers crossed. Hoping for the best, expecting the worst. " created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:58:31 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's even worse than it appears. " created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:58:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Still diggin!" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:59:06 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Etc." created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:59:11 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Experiment 3 appears to be a success" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:19:36 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="It would be helpful if everyone who sees this, whether or not you're in a Far East timezone, tries to build with the new CMS, just to test it out, so you have used it before it becomes the only option." created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:19:44 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The previous version is in pretty bad shape, I really want to get the new version installed and get beyond the date problems. " created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:20:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the URL:" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:20:59 GMT">
						<outline text="http://scripting.com/code/testing/experiment3/?name=cluelessnewbie" created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:21:07 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="I just tried it as if I were from Los Angeles, and there was a problem. Fixed it, now that and the other areas seem to work. " created="Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:21:45 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 27" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 12:55:43 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="27">
				<outline text="Experiment 3 is ready for you!" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 20:55:59 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Dear international friends!" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 20:56:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Experiment 3 is ready to go, I hope, I think, I pray. ;-)"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/code/testing/experiment3/?name=cluelessnewbie&quot;&gt;http://scripting.com/code/testing/experiment3/?name=cluelessnewbie&lt;/a&gt;" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 20:56:12 GMT"/>
					<outline text="When you test it out on your blog, just change &quot;cluelessnewbie&quot; to your username."/>
					<outline text="The first time it builds your blog it might take a few seconds." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 20:57:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="When it's ready it will respond with a link to the test version of your blog. The real version, the one your readers see, is not changed by this experiment. This is all happening in a temporary space. Just for this test. No actual blogs were harmed." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 20:57:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The thing to do then is to look it over and see if it got the timezone stuff right. And then look for any other errors. There has been a lot of rock and roll in Old School behind the scenes, but from your point of view it should be the same Old School you love (I hope) but without the timezone foolishness."/>
					<outline text="Then, try adding a post, and do it again. Did it work?"/>
					<outline text="Then, assuming you live east of New York -- India, Malaysia, China, Australia, New Zealand and the like, wait until it's the 29th where you are and it's still the 28th here. Of if you're in Europe and you act pretty fast, you can post something just after midnight or so, and it'll be a good test because then it will still be the 27th here." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 21:01:12 GMT"/>
					<outline text="What you should see is what you would expect based on where you are."/>
					<outline text="Please keep us apprised of what's happening by posting a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/88#issuecomment-953302207&quot;&gt;comment here&lt;/a&gt;." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 20:56:37 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Progress" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:04:25 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Well, here's something that works." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:04:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="My cluelessnewbie blog thinks it's in New Zealand where it is already the 28th." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:04:35 GMT"/>
					<outline text="That's nice. Now can you build the home page for such a blog?" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:04:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Yes, we &lt;a href=&quot;http://clueless.lucky.wtf/&quot;&gt;can&lt;/a&gt;." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:05:14 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And can we build an archive page for such a blog, even though the server is in NY where it is still the 27th? Wellllll..." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:05:18 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Ohhh &lt;a href=&quot;http://clueless.lucky.wtf/2021/10/28.html&quot;&gt;yes&lt;/a&gt;." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:05:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Note this is in a test server running locally. " created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 15:06:32 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Morning Drummer Notes" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 12:59:49 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/82#issuecomment-952450047&quot;&gt;Anton found&lt;/a&gt; a data-losing bug yesterday. Unfortunately I'm head-down right now on getting international blogs working properly, it's a big job that must be done, or else I would join Anton in figuring out what went wrong in this case. " created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:00:04 GMT" image="http://scripting.com/images/2021/06/14/strongman.png"/>
					<outline text="Meanwhile there is still a data-losing problem that was uncovered by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/82&quot;&gt;Scott Hanson&lt;/a&gt; ten days ago, similarly I have not been able to focus on that. But these are big issues. " created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:00:46 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Also yesterday, a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/99#issue-1036509784&quot;&gt;report&lt;/a&gt; from gwthompson that the Delete file command deleted a file when he pressed Cancel. I could not reproduce, and after a time, it stopped misbehaving on his machine. If you can confirm, that would be helpful. As always, steps to reproduce are essential. I might just rewrite the confirmation code, it could use it. Caveat: Only test with files you can afford to lose! :smile:" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:01:35 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Software maintenance is a lot like working on a car, or a human body. Sometimes parts wear out after years of use. You then have to roll up your sleeves and figure out what happened, and fix it. In software, unlike cars and humans, you always can fix it, but sometimes it's easier than others. A teaser, I came across some features in Old School that people have been asking for that I forgot were there. I will save those to write up for when I'm done with this project." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:06:47 GMT"/>
					<outline text="One more thing, I saw on a Drummer blog (I don't recall which one) someone said that adding links to outline text is very hard and that Markdown is easier. I wonder if people don't know how easy it is in Drummer. Here's how you do it..." created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:08:24 GMT">
						<outline text="To add a link select the word or phrase you want to link from, click the link icon in the left edge (it's the second one), paste the URL into the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/10/27/dialog.png&quot;&gt;dialog&lt;/a&gt; and click OK. That's it. " created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:09:42 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="The feature is &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/iconbar.opml#1630706867000&quot;&gt;documented&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:11:25 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I can't wait to be done with what has turned into a fairly major rewrite that is necessary. " created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:03:10 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="flCodeSubs for subs that are code" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 12:55:44 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Alex Johnstone, trailblazing Drummer blogger, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/100#issue-1037316578&quot;&gt;asks&lt;/a&gt; what's the best way to include bits of code in a Drummer post. The answer is to add an &lt;i&gt;flCodeSubs&lt;/i&gt; attribute on the parent of the code block, with a value of true. This should be in the blogging howto, but as yet is not. " created="Wed, 27 Oct 2021 12:55:52 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 26" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2021 12:07:00 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="26">
				<outline text="Update on The Big Date Bug" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2021 21:57:50 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Thanks for the help in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/code/testing/breakdownblogbydays/index.html?name=_am1t&quot;&gt;Second blog timeZone experiment&lt;/a&gt;, which showed that we do indeed have an algorithm that works that figures out what goes on the home page of a non-US blog using the blog's local time, at any time in the day or night.  " created="Tue, 26 Oct 2021 21:57:56 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I am now rewriting a fairly large part of Old School around this algorithm. It's the equivalent of open heart surgery. But not as dangerous. " created="Tue, 26 Oct 2021 21:59:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Once the work is done, maybe in a day or two, then we will do the &lt;i&gt;Third blog timeZone experiment, &lt;/i&gt;on a test server, running far away from the deployed version, so we risk nothing, and once that is verified, we can proceed as if this never happened! â¤ï¸" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2021 22:03:05 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="You can script your Drummer file backups" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2021 12:07:01 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Alex Johnstone &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/63#issuecomment-951849007&quot;&gt;explains&lt;/a&gt;. He does it in Python, but you could probably get it to work in Drummer. " created="Tue, 26 Oct 2021 12:09:28 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 25" created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 13:39:40 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="25">
				<outline text="This is what system-level scripting is for" created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 20:30:34 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/83#issuecomment-951277662&quot;&gt;Taking steps&lt;/a&gt; out of processes we do a lot of. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 20:30:41 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's not glamorous, just useful. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 20:30:55 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Second blog timeZone experiment" created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:06:12 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="First thanks for all the participation in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/code/testing/whatdayisit/index.html&quot;&gt;first timeZone experiment&lt;/a&gt;. I am now confident we have an algorithm that gets the numeric values for month, day and year, &lt;i&gt;in the blog's local time zone&lt;/i&gt; for each post, and now believe we can accurately sort them out into baskets, by day. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:06:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This will make it possible to restructure the code that builds the home page and the daily and monthly archive pages, so that they work across all time zones. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 22:05:56 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The next test is to try sorting actual blog.opml files. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:09:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="For example, I have temporarily changed the timeZoneOffset attribute for &lt;a href=&quot;http://clueless.lucky.wtf/&quot;&gt;cluelessnewbie&lt;/a&gt; to 12, which means it's now already the 26th according to my blog. And sure enough the top two posts that I just created appear in the sorting in the 26th. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:09:49 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the link I used to test that." created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:10:49 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/code/testing/breakdownblogbydays/?name=cluelessnewbie&quot;&gt;http://scripting.com/code/testing/breakdownblogbydays/?name=cluelessnewbie&lt;/a&gt;" created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:10:56 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You can run the test against your blog by changing the name parameter on the URL to the name you use for your Drummer account, and see if the algorithm correctly sorts your posts into days. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:11:01 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/88#issuecomment-951088327&quot;&gt;Report the results here&lt;/a&gt;. Be sure to include your name, so we can run the test too. " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:12:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Thanks for the help. This has been a uniquely cooperative process, for what is a surprisingly difficult problem. ;-)" created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 16:12:42 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Update to default template CSS" created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 13:39:41 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/98#issue-1034737224&quot;&gt;Amit&lt;/a&gt; for the report of two errors in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/code/drummercms/templates/minimal/styles.css&quot;&gt;default template CSS&lt;/a&gt; for Drummer blogs." created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 13:39:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/98#issuecomment-950939742&quot;&gt;While I was there&lt;/a&gt; I found a third omission, and fixed it, " created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 13:42:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Net result of these changes -- your sites should work better on phone-size devices." created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 13:42:45 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 23" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:03:44 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="23">
				<outline text="Another timezone approach" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:09:42 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="OK -- once I &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/2021/10/23/131437.html?title=timezonesArrrgh&quot;&gt;gave up&lt;/a&gt; on getting it done today, I started to think about the problem differently." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:09:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="As you can hear in my &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/23/progressReportOnDateStuff.m4a&quot;&gt;second voicemail&lt;/a&gt;, the question that was so hard to answer is this:" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:28:37 GMT">
						<outline text="What day is it in the location the user is in?" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:10:03 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="It's just an algorithm, it must be possible to get the computer to figure that out. So I put together this little app." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:13:39 GMT">
						<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/code/testing/whatdayisit/&quot;&gt;http://scripting.com/code/testing/whatdayisit/&lt;/a&gt;" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:10:52 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="I'm turning to my friends around the world to check this little app, over the course of a day and let me know if it's got it right." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:11:59 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Comment &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/88#issuecomment-950206243&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:12:00 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Timezones arrrgh" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:14:37 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I didn't make any progress on the problem, and my work day is over." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:56:53 GMT">
						<outline text="So -- here's the thing, I'm not  going to be able to work on this for a bit, and when I do, it's going to be with a test server." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:57:04 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Bottom line -- dates are weird, and we're pushing up against the limits of the language here. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:57:25 GMT"/>
						<outline text="It's time to take a step back, work on some other stuff for a while, and come back to this with a fresh perspective." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:57:47 GMT"/>
						<outline text="What this means is, if you're hit by this issue, finding a way to work with it until the problems are fixed. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:58:04 GMT"/>
						<outline text="That happens sometimes, I want nothing more than to put this behind us, but it isn't going to happen in the next few days. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:58:34 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Here's the report from this morning" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:56:43 GMT">
						<outline text="I swear I'm going to have this nailed by end of business today." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:14:52 GMT"/>
						<outline text="It's all math, but it's really confusing when you're in one time zone and the users are far away in different time zones." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:15:04 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Thanks to Amit for championing this. ðŸ‘" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:15:23 GMT"/>
						<outline text="A &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/23/moreThoughtsOnTimeZonesAndBlogs.m4a&quot;&gt;voicemail&lt;/a&gt; on the zen of timezones in blogging. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 14:34:06 GMT"/>
						<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/23/progressReportOnDateStuff.m4a&quot;&gt;Progress report&lt;/a&gt;. Not going very well, JS is not cooperating. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 16:40:13 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="PagePark fix" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:32:20 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Fixed default error page for sites using PagePark and hosting over HTTPS" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:32:58 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It was loading a font and an image over HTTP which is a no-no." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:32:33 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Publishing to WordPress gets started" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:09:42 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Frank Meeuwsen is &lt;a href=&quot;http://oldschool.scripting.com/frankmeeuwsen/2021/10/23/065437.html?title=publishToWordpressWithDrummer&quot;&gt;working&lt;/a&gt; on a script to publish to WordPress from his Drummer outline. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:09:57 GMT" isComment="false"/>
					<outline text="He says heâ€™s not a programmer, but reading his code, heâ€™s figured a bunch of stuff out." created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:10:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's a &lt;i&gt;perfect&lt;/i&gt; use of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerRFC/issues/1&quot;&gt;new RFC site&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:10:16 GMT"/>
					<outline text="We can fill in all the details as far as Drummer is concerned, so don't worry about that. The important contribution here is that Frank is digging in to the WordPress API, one that I have looked at and not grokked. So just focus on getting that part right, and I'm happy to add new verbs to the language to support this connection. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:10:55 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I can imagine a class of verbs for WordPress, it's that important a product for Drummer to connect to. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:12:10 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Drummer has a new bookmarklet" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:03:45 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="It's &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/general.opml#1634950078000&quot;&gt;documented&lt;/a&gt; on the FAQs page. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:03:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You install it in the usual way, by dragging a bit of text to the icon bar in your browser, also known as its &quot;chrome.&quot;" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:04:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Think of it as a way to save a link to something on the web without leaving a tab open in the browser. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:04:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The clip is added to the calendar structure of your Notes outline. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:07:34 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If you have comments or questions, I started a thread &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/96&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Sat, 23 Oct 2021 13:05:15 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 22" created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 13:15:59 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="22">
				<outline text="Bug for non-American blogs" created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 13:16:00 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="It's a timezone issue, thanks to Amit for finding it, reporting it, and re-reporting it. " created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 13:16:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's a nasty one because it moves around, and depends on what time of day he started blogging, believe it or not." created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 13:16:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If you're sufficiently east of the US, and you start blogging early in the day (relatively) you might not see today's posts on your home page. " created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 13:17:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This will be fixed shortly, but I wanted to give you all a heads up in case you're seeing this, you're not losing your mind. ðŸ˜›" created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 13:17:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Follow along in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/88&quot;&gt;this thread&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 13:18:31 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Update: Two problems were &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/88#issuecomment-949702524&quot;&gt;found and fixed&lt;/a&gt; and now Amit's blog is building correctly. " created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 15:19:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There's a new release of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/oldSchoolBlog&quot;&gt;Old School&lt;/a&gt; with the fixes and the new version is deployed on the server. " created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 15:20:01 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And now I will take a much-needed break. ðŸ˜€ " created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 15:21:01 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Update at 6PM Eastern -- more work needed tomorrow, we have the problem solved for India, but still more to do for New Zealand. Amit has been a huge help." created="Fri, 22 Oct 2021 21:50:14 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 21" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:24:48 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="21">
				<outline text="A new version of Public Folder app" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 20:52:26 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/83&quot;&gt;Amit Gawande&lt;/a&gt; has been trying to figure out the workflow for images from his desktop, to the web and back into web Drummer. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 20:52:33 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Electric Drummer already has this facility built into it, but Amit can't use E/D for his application, since he has to be able to edit his blog from multiple locations. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 20:54:33 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I suggested he try my &lt;a href=&quot;http://publicfolder.io/&quot;&gt;Public Folder&lt;/a&gt; app. I was hoping he would use it because then I would have someone who could test its use with Drummer in a real world setting, and work with me to create a smooth workflow for people working from the web Drummer. It really helps to have another human being with the perspective of a user as something is developing. And I wanted to solve the problem not just for E/D for for web Drummer too." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 20:55:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="So, I had an idea how this might work, but unfortunately it wasn't possible to connect from the web browser to a local web server, which is actually what the Public Folder app is. We had a lot of fun with &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/davenet/1997/09/14/FractionalHorsepowerHTTPSe.html&quot;&gt;fractional horsepower http servers&lt;/a&gt; in Frontier in the 90s, but the powers that be thought this was a security problem (it likely is) so that avenue is no longer open. Tis a shame. We were so much more innocent then! :boom:" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 20:56:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Then I had the idea that since Public Folder is able to write files to S3, and Drummer scripts can read those files, that might work. And -- &lt;i&gt;tadahh&lt;/i&gt; -- it did work, resulting in version 0.4.8 of &lt;a href=&quot;http://this.how/publicFolder/&quot;&gt;Public Folder&lt;/a&gt;, which is now available for download. The instructions on &lt;a href=&quot;http://this.how/publicFolder/#1634847088000&quot;&gt;how to set up&lt;/a&gt; are also on that page. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 20:57:55 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I was sure at some time Public Folder would come in handy for others. I already depend on it myself for all my this.how style outlines, including the docs for Drummer, which are all uploaded publicly via Public Folder." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 21:00:35 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The idea of Public Folder, btw, was to replace the public folder &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/stories/2011/04/25/publicDropboxWithoutTheLoc.html&quot;&gt;Dropbox used to have&lt;/a&gt; which it phased out. It was an important thing." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 21:01:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I think eventually all my apps will fit into &lt;i&gt;The World of Drummer&lt;/i&gt; in some way. It's like the Marvel Universe or a big family reunion. :heart:" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 21:02:08 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I'm not keeping up with the error reports" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:12:07 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I know the rope is slipping through my hands. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:12:16 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I try to spend some time each day looking at fixing bugs, but I have to move forward on other fronts too, and I only spend about 4-5 hours working on this stuff every day. Any more than that is a waste of time, I lose productivity, burn myself out, am unhappy and eventually it makes me sick. Not that you wanted to know all that. ;-)" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:12:23 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Sometimes I can't dig in because I don't understand what happened, because (honestly) the reports are not well specificed, or well written. People can help out by trying to get reproducible steps, that makes it a quicker job for me, more likely to result in a fix, rather than wasted time. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:13:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Sometimes I can't dig in because I just can't get there. Esp problems in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/concord&quot;&gt;Concord&lt;/a&gt;, the core outliner. It is open source, so other people can work on that. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:15:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: One of the things on my todo list is to update the Concord repo with my latest fixes." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:17:03 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="A place for Drummer RFCs" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:02:32 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I started a new GitHub repo called &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerRFC/blob/main/README.md&quot;&gt;DrummerRFC&lt;/a&gt;." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:02:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Read the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerRFC/blob/main/README.md&quot;&gt;readme&lt;/a&gt; with some care before posting an &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Request_for_Comments&quot;&gt;RFC&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:04:13 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's not for support and bug reports, that's what the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues&quot;&gt;support site&lt;/a&gt; is for." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:04:35 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's also not a community site, not a place to promote yourself, or your projects. It's a place to try out ideas, get feedback or buy-in, to initiate collaboration. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:04:47 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You're still on your own for community, this is not something I want to be involved in at this time. But I do want to share ideas. In fact I have an RFC I plan to write myself, for a feature that I'm not ready yet to release because I want to hear what people think first. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:05:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="But please before you post anything there, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerRFC/blob/main/README.md&quot;&gt;read the readme&lt;/a&gt;. It's important. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:06:12 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Drummer and Gatsby" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:27:27 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://oldschool.scripting.com/ScottHansonDE/2021/10/21/100522.html?title=connectingDrummerToGatsby&quot;&gt;Scott Hanson&lt;/a&gt; has Drummer hooked up to Gatsby." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:28:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I love this. Scott has been an incredible contributor to Drummer since we started testing in August. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:28:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="He picked up work done by Andrew Shell, who was the first user, after myself -- and wrote the core code in the preprocessor for JavaSxript. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:29:07 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Combined, they made Drummer work with Gatsby. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:29:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="All because we deliberately made that possible by using an open format, OPML." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:30:06 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the real punchline. I've never used Gatsby, yet my product works with it. " created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:30:28 GMT"/>
					<outline text="As they say..." created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:30:42 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Bing!&lt;/i&gt;" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2021 13:30:45 GMT"/>
					</outline>
