			<outline text="October 18" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 13:52:23 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="18">
				<outline text="Micro.blog and Drummer" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 21:03:47 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/18/microblogAndDrummerFTW.m4a&quot;&gt;12-minute podcast&lt;/a&gt; about this fantastic new connection." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 21:37:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/04/03/133021.html?title=theMakingOfDrummer&quot;&gt;initial post&lt;/a&gt; I mentioned in the podcast. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 21:41:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Just before Drummer shipped I sent an email to Manton Reece, the developer and runner of micro.blog, asking if he was interested in being the first blogging system to hook up with Drummer via the OPML bridge. The same interface we use in Drummer to connect to Old School. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 21:03:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.manton.org/2021/10/18/drummer-and-microblog.html&quot;&gt;Well here it is&lt;/a&gt;. He works fast. ;-)" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 21:04:46 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Just watched the video -- I &lt;i&gt;love&lt;/i&gt; how he did it. Beautiful. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 21:09:10 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Docs work" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:30:55 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I'm going to spend the rest of the day planning another pass over the docs." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:30:58 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I want to make it easier for me to move stuff from the Change Notes outline to the docs." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:31:12 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Right now imho it's too hard to find things. I want to improve that too. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:31:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I watched Anton try to help someone find the docs for the header image att. That should be both memorable and quick, and it's neither of those things at this point." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:31:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I very much consider docs an integral part of this product, not an afterthought. We're going to make the docs better and better, just as we do with the software. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:32:14 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Workflow for images" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:25:18 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="There was a discussion about workflow for images in web Drummer yesterday, and it got me thinking of how it should work, and I think I figured it out, at least for people who have Amazon accounts and know how to set up an S3 location. It's a good skill to have, and I wish Amazon made it easier, it shouldn't be anywhere near as hard as it is, esp if all you want to do is store small images there. But as they say it is what it is." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:25:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There are other answers possible, but mine is to use the &lt;a href=&quot;http://this.how/publicFolder/&quot;&gt;PublicFolder&lt;/a&gt; app. I checked and it has a HTTP server built in, and therefore a simple interface can be created through a Drummer script, to get the last image you published and put it on the bar cursor headline as an image attribute. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:26:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This is how I do it on Electric Drummer except the PublicFolder functionality is baked in. There is a note in the blogging how to about how to set it up. It's only complicated because Amazon makes it so. Sorry. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:27:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Anyway, the bridge between PublicFolder and Drummer is not built yet. I have a bit of work to do to get PF current with the latest Electron stuff. But it's definitely on my todo list. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:28:32 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Changed prompt for the Edit OPML Headers command" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:23:13 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="It now includes the name of file whose head-level atts you're editing.  " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:23:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/10/18/headAttDialogPrompt.png&quot;&gt;Screen shot&lt;/a&gt;." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:24:12 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Fixed problem for HTTPS users" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:19:16 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="There was a problem in how the default template worked for people who were using HTTPS for their blog. It's a long story, but it meant that they couldn't use the About panel, and I want you all to use them, so when I read your blog I have an idea who's speaking. ;-)" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:19:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I fixed the problem by making Old School read the outline pointed to by urlAboutOpml. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:20:25 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And the outline is baked into the home page of the site, via a macro called [%aboutOutline%]." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:21:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If you've created a custom version of the template, you'll need to add a bit of code to it. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:22:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="More details in this &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/78#issuecomment-945941809&quot;&gt;comment&lt;/a&gt; on the thread for HTTPS support." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:21:48 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 17" created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:25:53 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="17">
				<outline text="Style note -- singular items before titled items" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:11:57 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="On Scripting News I always put the singular items ahead of the titled items. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:12:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's hard on the readers if you don't do it this way, because the singular items that follow a titled item appear to be part of the titled item. The delineation isn't easy to spot. It's possible that there's a visual way to keep them sorted out, but I don't know what it is. So I put all the singular items first. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:12:45 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's an &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/15.html&quot;&gt;example&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:14:42 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Style note -- links in blog post titles" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:10:51 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I see people including links in the titles of their posts." created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:10:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In general this isn't done on the web. Not sure why, but it's jarring to see a post that links from the title. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:11:03 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's an &lt;a href=&quot;https://cannabiscto.com/2021/10/17/213921.html?title=theStoreHasAPresenceOnGoogleMyBusiness&quot;&gt;example&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 03:11:36 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Starting a new doc" created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:50:29 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://drummer.scripting.com/davewiner/drummer/general.opml&quot;&gt;General tips&lt;/a&gt;." created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:50:34 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This is for topics that are not specific to outlining, scripting, etc." created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:50:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="First item is going to be about backing up! " created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:51:04 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I'm also thinking of making that the first item on the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/about.opml&quot;&gt;About page&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:51:14 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="A tab-related problem" created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:35:48 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Scott Hanson &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/82&quot;&gt;reports&lt;/a&gt; on a problem that was reported last night by Alex Johnstone. " created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:35:57 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/38#issuecomment-945090274&quot;&gt;similar issue&lt;/a&gt; reported this morning by @ambiprospect. (No name on his profile page.)" created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:38:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The must be a reason these are all showing up now, but I can't think of why. Maybe when we figure out what it is, it'll be apparent. But there have been zero changes in anything core in Drummer in the last week. I consider the software stable, so I don't want to screw around with that, esp when the rollout is going so well. " created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:40:56 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Reproducible steps are going to be the key to solving this. I will be taking a look at the source code based on the reports and seeing if that helps to understand where there might be a problem. " created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:42:06 GMT"/>
					<outline text="We've had problems like this with Drummer in development." created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:43:06 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Reproducible steps" created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:25:54 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="When we catch a problem in the software, before we can fix it we need to be able to reproduce it. " created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:25:58 GMT"/>
					<outline text="We're looking at what might be a serious problem in the tabs in Drummer, I'll have more on it shortly, but in this case as in all serious testing work, the reproducible steps are the only way you can get a problem fixed with any certainty. " created="Sun, 17 Oct 2021 13:26:25 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 16" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:39:37 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="16">
