				<outline text="HTTPS project is rolling" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:40:31 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/tmanternach&quot;&gt;Trevor Manternach&lt;/a&gt; for taking the lead. " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:40:45 GMT"/>
					<outline text="A bunch of the other smart techies are working with him. " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:41:09 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I love to see this kind of cooperative development. " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:41:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And I've been able to just watch, that's the best part. ðŸ˜€" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:41:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/78&quot;&gt;thread&lt;/a&gt;." created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:41:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And here's Trevor's &lt;a href=&quot;https://trevormanternach.com/&quot;&gt;blog&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:28:30 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Whoa" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:39:38 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I just lost my first two change notes for the morning. How did that happen? Oy. " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:40:10 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Replaced the one about HTTPS, above." created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:42:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The other said I'm deleting requests for help that don't have any information other than something they did didn't work the way they thought it should. No one has the time to coax the relevant info out of the person. If you want help, you have a basic responsibility to respect the person you're asking for help from. " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:42:59 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Also noted that a lot of times the problem is web caching. Learn how to get your browser to do a hard reload. Always try that first. Once you have that mastered, it's amazing how much time you'll save.  " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:43:47 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Postscript. I didn't lose them. I put them in the wrong outline. Operator malfunction." created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 13:47:02 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 15" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:05:05 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="15">
				<outline text="Sharing links into Drummer outlines" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:05:06 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&quot;The link opens an outline in Drummer.&quot;" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:05:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You may have noticed me saying this in the last few days." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:05:11 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Now I'm going to show you how to do it yourself." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:05:35 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There's a new command in the DW menu, which is explained in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/scripting.opml#1627745102000&quot;&gt;Scripting howto&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:06:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The command is in the Utilities sub-menu of the DW menu. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:06:31 GMT"/>
					<outline text="How it works." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:07:30 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
						<outline text="Put the bar cursor on any headline in a public outline." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:07:34 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Choose the &lt;i&gt;I/O Permalink&lt;/i&gt; command in the Utilities sub-menu of the DW menu." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:07:46 GMT"/>
						<outline text="It confirms you want to create a public link to the bar cursor headline." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:07:52 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Drummer opens with that outline open with the bar cursor on the headline." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:08:13 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="You can share that URL with others. Try it yourself." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:08:39 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
						<outline text="Copy the URL from the browser's address bar." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:12:59 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Close the Drummer tab. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:08:52 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Paste the URL in the browser's address bar. Press Return." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:08:57 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Drummer should open with the outline open and the cursor on the headline." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:09:09 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="If you have questions, comments or want to see the source code, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/75&quot;&gt;go here&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 14:09:35 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="HTTPS" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:36:42 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="It's totally okay if you want to have an HTTPS gateway to your Drummer blog. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:36:46 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There is an HTTPS address for the S3 bucket containing the rendered blogs:" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:37:16 GMT">
						<outline text="https://s3.amazonaws.com/oldschool.scripting.com/" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:37:36 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Give it a try. Let us know if it works! :-)" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:37:37 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Update: Trevor Manternach &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/78&quot;&gt;posted&lt;/a&gt; an HTTPS howto. " created="Sat, 16 Oct 2021 01:44:12 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Permalinks and the docs" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:36:34 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I'm sure you've noticed that permalinks didn't work reliably in the Drummer docs." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:36:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I want to revisit how the outlines are rendered, I want much less of it to happen every time the page is accessed. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:36:57 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In the meantime, I've found that if I turn off the glossary for these files, permalinks do work." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:37:39 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's an &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/scripting.opml#1628514152000&quot;&gt;example&lt;/a&gt;. It should take you The iconbar section of the Scripting howto." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:37:57 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I also don't like the menu on the side. I might change it to work like the &lt;a href=&quot;http://opml.org/&quot;&gt;opml.org&lt;/a&gt; site. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:38:46 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Quotes in file titles" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:16:14 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="A long-time bug -- if a file title has a single-quote character, the display of the tab title will be screwed up. I've seen this before and tried to fix it unsuccessfully in August. I took another stab at it today, and it appears to be fixed on my machine." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:16:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There's a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/74#issuecomment-944429247&quot;&gt;thread&lt;/a&gt; on this -- if you've seen the problem and it's now either fixed or not, please report. Thanks. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:17:34 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I bumped the version to 2.0.10." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 16:18:35 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Another support request" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:30:55 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="If I help you get a problem solved, please..." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:31:00 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
						<outline text="Let me know if it worked. I'm going to keep thinking it might be a problem, esp for others, until I hear back from you that it cured your problem. I'm not just helping you to help you, it's to help others too. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:31:09 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Pay it back. If I helped you solve the problem, then when someone else pops up with the same problem, help them. It's how we build a community here. Otherwise it just burns itself out. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:31:55 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I only work about four to five hours a day" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:19:15 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I've got a routine. Right now all my time is being spent helping people with urgent matters, but the thing is, most of them are not actually urgent." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:19:28 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This week is unusual. Next week I'd like to spend most of my working time fixing problems and moving forward with the software. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:20:13 GMT"/>
					<outline text="What can't change is the amount of time I work each day. I used to be willing to push it way too far, and that got me sick. I just can't do that anymore." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:20:55 GMT"/>
					<outline text="So try to be aware of that, right now I am the support for this product. No one else can do it. People are trying to pitch in and that's much appreciated." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:21:21 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's got to settle down, a bunch. If you feel exhausted and upset, then slow down, take a breath, we tend to get very urgent as we do our web thing. That's not a way to relate in a community like this. Go for a walk or a whatever you to do to relax, then take another look at the problem. It often happens that by the time you get back you've figured out what the problem is. If not, then carefully write up what you did, what you expected to happen, etc. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:21:52 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="When you post a request for help..." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:48:53 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="A common mistake is to assume the person reading the request is there with you. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:49:00 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You have to give us some basic information. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:49:14 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If it's about your blog, what's the address of your blog.opml file. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:49:21 GMT"/>
					<outline text="How can we guess how the CMS is dealing with your blog if we don't know what you sent to it?" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:49:34 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Common sense. Empathy. And if you really want help you have to think about what info someone is going to need to help you." created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:49:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="More &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2020/12/12/165429.html?title=howToAskForHelpWithSoftware&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.  And &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2014/03/19/howToAskForHelpWithSoftware.html&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:50:23 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And here's a &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2014/09/21/theLostArtOfSoftwareTesting.html&quot;&gt;bit&lt;/a&gt; about the lost art of software testing. " created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 20:51:52 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 14" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:06:56 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="14">
				<outline text="Changing PagePark advice" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:33:32 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="In the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/blogging.opml#1628776787000&quot;&gt;section&lt;/a&gt; of the Blogging howto where we discuss how to use &lt;a href=&quot;http://pagepark.io/&quot;&gt;PagePark&lt;/a&gt; to create a custom URL for your Drummer blog, I changed the recommendation for how to do it. The new way does not require a complex setup of Amazon credentials. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:33:42 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="A working R3 bookmarklet?" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:35:17 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Jack Baty has posted a Radio3 bookmarklet written by John Johnston that supposedly works. Somewhere along the line, the one on the Radio3 site broke? As Jack says it's been hard for me to respond to all the fires that have been burning, but I'm really glad these guys did. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:35:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/71&quot;&gt;Here's the link&lt;/a&gt;. If the consensus is that it works, I'll update the Radio3 site. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:36:27 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Thanks! I totally appreciate the help. ðŸ˜€" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:36:41 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="New head-level attribute -- timeZoneOffset" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:17:09 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="There's a new &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/blogging.opml#1634213853000&quot;&gt;section&lt;/a&gt; in the Blogging howto, about getting the time zone of your blog right. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:17:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Thanks to Amit and Scott for their help testing this feature. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:18:36 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If you have questions, this is &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/64&quot;&gt;where&lt;/a&gt; you go. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:18:03 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="New server code releases" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:42:19 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="New versions of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/oldSchoolBlog&quot;&gt;oldSchoolBlog&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerCms&quot;&gt;drummerCms&lt;/a&gt;." created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:07:04 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Drummer is a scripting system" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:37:22 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="The focus has been on Drummer as a blogging tool, and I couldn't be happier with the response. I think we have gotten the initial glitches taken care of, and now I can step back and take a deep breath and start to think about what's next." created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:37:28 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In the meantime, if you're a script person, and I think a bunch of you are, have a look at the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/scripting.opml&quot;&gt;scripting howto&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:38:07 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I have an interesting new script I want to share with you, in the morning." created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:38:58 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In the meantime as a former Californian and a baseball fan since childhood, I have a game to watch tonight. And of course I'm rooting for the Giants. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:39:10 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Thanks!" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:39:56 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I don't know where all you lovely people came from. " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:39:59 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Were you always there? " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:43:44 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In any case, please stick with Drummer, we're just getting started. â¤ï¸ " created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 22:43:48 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 13" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:56:05 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="13">
				<outline text="Custom URL for your Drummer blog" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 15:22:21 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="There are a number of people who want to use Drummer to host a blog using their own domain." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 15:22:33 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The instructions on the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/blogging.opml#1628776787000&quot;&gt;blogging page&lt;/a&gt; only worked for the home page, the subordinate page links would still point to oldschool.scripting.com." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 15:23:29 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I thought we'd have to use custom installs of drummerCms to solve the problem, but along the way I found a simpler approach which I have implemented."/>
					<outline text="Basically the instructions on the Blogging page now work, with an additional step."/>
					<outline text="There's a new head-level attribute called urlBlogWebsite, which tells drummerCms where the links should point."/>
					<outline text="It works. I've set it up for clueless.lucky.wtf. Click around. The links all stay within the domain."/>
					<outline text="Now, you still need a server, and need to set up PagePark. But this is a lot easier than setting up drummerCms."/>
					<outline text="Please &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/67&quot;&gt;let me know&lt;/a&gt; if it works or you have problems." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 15:22:44 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Why we use Twitter identity" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 14:05:00 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I made this a &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/13/140500.html?title=whyWeUseTwitterIdentiy&quot;&gt;blog post&lt;/a&gt;." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 14:12:58 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="If something isn't working" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:43:47 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="And you can't figure out what went wrong..." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:43:55 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Two things to try that you might not thought of.." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:44:05 GMT">
						<outline text="Hard reload the app" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:44:13 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Open the JavaScript console and see if there are any error messages." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:44:27 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="When you think the software isn't working, that's the problem, if there were error messages in the console, try to include them in your report. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 14:03:10 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Security questions for Electric Drummer" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:57:30 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="When you launch E/D for the first time, you are told the author of the program can't be verified and the Mac will refuse to launch it. Hope is not lost!" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:57:41 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Open the System Preferences app." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:58:12 GMT" image="http://scripting.com/images/2021/10/20/openAnyway.png"/>
					<outline text="Click on the Security &amp; Privacy button." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:58:23 GMT"/>
					<outline text="At the bottom of the display you'll see an option to load the app anyway." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:58:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="That's the thing to do." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:59:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="People have noted that the mod date is in 2020, that's because that's the mod date of the Electron package. I can probably fix that, and will attempt to do so. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:59:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="People have noted that the app is big. Yes it is. That's because there's a full browser and Node stack in the package. Drummer itself is quite small. This is the way it works in 2021. You have to bring the browser and operating system with you on trips to the Mac. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:59:59 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Luckily today's machines have &lt;i&gt;lots&lt;/i&gt; of memory!" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:00:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And Drummer is nice and fast. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:01:05 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Dark mode" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:56:06 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Frequently asked question about Dark Mode. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:56:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="How to turn back to light mode? " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:56:18 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Reload." created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:56:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This even works in Electric Drummer. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:56:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="All the way at the top of the screen, there's a menu Window menu, with a Reload command. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:56:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It has the same effect. " created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 12:57:08 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 12" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 12:33:32 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="12">
				<outline text="Update on blogging on your own domain" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 19:32:58 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I've reviewed the code in drummerCms, and I'm 99 percent sure we'll be able to set it up so you can run your own CMS and put the pages in your own S3 bucket. I think that'll probably be ready tomorrow, knock wood, praise murphy." created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 19:33:06 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You will have to run a server to get that feature though. But there will be no programming involved. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 19:33:59 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Drummer's key scripting innovation" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 16:58:17 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="There's a huge innovation in the JavaScript runtime in Drummer. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 16:58:25 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I wrote up an example illustrating the new thing in &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/03/24/161331.html?title=drummersKeyInnovation&quot;&gt;a blog post&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 16:58:36 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="How to set up a Unix system for Node apps that write to S3" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:43:42 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Some Drummer users are trying to get &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerCms&quot;&gt;drummerCms&lt;/a&gt; to work on their servers, so they can publish to a custom domain. To do so you have to set up your system so that Node apps can read and write to S3 via Amazon's API. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:44:07 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I've been telling people to &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ses/latest/DeveloperGuide/create-shared-credentials-file.html&quot;&gt;follow Amazons directions&lt;/a&gt;. I just reviewed them and they seem pretty straightforward. But they could be a tiny bit easier, so I wrote these instructions. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:45:55 GMT">
						<outline text="At the command line type this:" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:57:53 GMT">
							<outline text="cd ~/.aws" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:55:19 GMT"/>
							<outline text="nano credentials" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:56:01 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="Paste &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/scripting/054e8430d870f85438208635bf6fc05a&quot;&gt;this text&lt;/a&gt;, replacing the dummy values with the ones from your AWS account:" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:56:40 GMT">
							<outline text="[default]&lt;br&gt;aws_access_key_id=tz4nhbttfvll76gb9ej7&lt;br&gt;aws_secret_access_key=cedx5jixadnwca1e3fnopkg8ji6cvynx4nlhgpy8" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:57:16 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="Type this:" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:57:21 GMT">
							<outline text="Control-O" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:57:34 GMT"/>
							<outline text="Return" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:57:43 GMT"/>
							<outline text="Control-X" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:57:45 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="Make sure the file was correctly created." created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:58:30 GMT">
							<outline text="cat credentials" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:58:48 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Having done all that, the app that tried to write to S3 should now be able to do it without error. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 15:59:03 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The Drummer blog" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 12:33:33 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Want to be sure you all know about the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/&quot;&gt;Drummer blog&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 12:33:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It has an RSS feed, of course, and you can subscribe to it in your favorite reader. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 12:34:02 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The thing I want to point out is that the blog and the Change Notes outline are the same thing. The text you're reading also appears &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/2021/10/12/123333.html?title=theDrummerBlog&quot;&gt;on the blog&lt;/a&gt;. It's kind of a unified field theory of writing for the web. It's all outlines, from top to bottom. And imho that's as it should be. ðŸ˜€" created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 12:34:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I think there are very strong advantages to subscribing to the outline in an outliner, that we're just beginning to explore this communication medium. We used it in the early 2000s at UserLand, with the right team, it really works. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 12:35:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If you want to get an idea of what I/O is about, I recommend this &lt;a href=&quot;https://bhc3.com/2009/01/16/before-there-was-twitter-there-was-dave-winers-instant-outliner/&quot;&gt;2009 piece&lt;/a&gt; by Hutch Carpenter. " created="Tue, 12 Oct 2021 12:36:03 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 11" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 12:52:24 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="11">
				<outline text="We can now handle users whose names begin with underscores" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:44:45 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="It's really easy to back up" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:04:47 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="So you should do it &lt;i&gt;now&lt;/i&gt; and do it often!" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:04:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's what you have to do" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:05:01 GMT">
						<outline text="1. Choose &lt;i&gt;Download my files&lt;/i&gt; from the Tools menu." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:05:05 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="That's it. It downloads a zip archive of all your files on the server, separated into two folders, one for private files, the other for public files." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:05:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You should do it before and after every work session. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:06:14 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The launch is a success" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:19:26 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Unqualified, absolutely great response. Everyone seems to love Drummer. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:19:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the number, there have been 950 page loads of drummer.scripting.com on Monday." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:19:49 GMT"/>
					<outline text="That's like saying your app was launched 950 times. That's fantastic. I would be happy if that's as large as the user base ever got. Because we can go somewhere with these users. And that's what I wanted. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:20:01 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;img src=&quot;http://static.scripting.com/larryKing/images/2014/03/13/curly.gif&quot;&gt;" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:20:41 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="We're getting technical users" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:18:01 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Yippee! I am so happy that we're getting people using Drummer who know how to run servers. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:18:07 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This could make a bunch of things possible." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:19:02 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Stay tuned..." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:18:33 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Server restarted at 3PM" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:03:28 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I had to restart the server just now to make a configuration change. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 19:03:35 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="New Twitter account -- @drummeroutliner" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 14:58:10 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I edited the old @littleoutliner account, changed its name, images. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 14:58:20 GMT">
						<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/drummeroutliner&quot;&gt;https://twitter.com/drummeroutliner&lt;/a&gt;" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 14:59:14 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="They aren't as clever as GitHub, the old account doesn't redirect. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 14:59:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I guess someone else could grab littleoutliner. Oy!" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 15:10:55 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Twitter and Facebook metadata" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 14:56:30 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="A detail that slipped through the cracks, the Twitter and Facebook metadata in the Drummer home page still were about Little Outliner. So I took a new screen shot, and fixed up the links and description. And went ahead and linked to Drummer on both Twitter and Facebook. It had already been discussed on Twitter, but not linked to. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 14:56:38 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="PagePark builds again" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 13:50:25 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I was working with a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/30#issuecomment-940060491&quot;&gt;user&lt;/a&gt; last night who wanted to use PagePark to provide his own domain name for his Drummer blog. This is very much a supported and recommended thing to do. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 13:50:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="However, when he installed and ran PagePark it failed. On further investigation it broke due to the dateformat change I &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/09/29/133747.html?title=theDateformatModule&quot;&gt;documented&lt;/a&gt; on Scripting News, that same one that took down the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/oldschoolblog&quot;&gt;oldSchoolBlog&lt;/a&gt; package. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 14:06:13 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I did a quick survey of all my code, I use dateformat everywhere. This is a first class mess. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 13:52:04 GMT" collapse="true">
						<outline text="What's even more interesting is that he had the problem on Glitch, where I don't believe they give you the option of what version of Node to install. If that's true then dateformat broke Glitch too. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 13:52:25 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="In any case -- for today -- I just updated the two bits of code that PagePark uses that broke, they are &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/daverss&quot;&gt;daverss&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/githubpub&quot;&gt;githubpub&lt;/a&gt;. I fixed them, published the new versions to NPM, updated my local test PagePark install and it boots up. Problem solved. So now we can proceed with the coolness of getting a $5 a month server to front for this user's Drummer blog." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 13:53:50 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Good morning! ðŸ˜€" created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 12:50:42 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="For all the newbies, welcome to the Change Notes outline for Drummer." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 12:50:44 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This is where I (Dave) report on new features and fixes in Drummer and related projects." created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 12:51:00 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Today, I want to invite new Drummer users to say hi, and let us know what you think, and ask whatever questions you may have. Not promising we'll have answers for all of them, but we'll try. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 12:51:16 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport/issues/57&quot;&gt;place&lt;/a&gt; for those notes/questions. " created="Mon, 11 Oct 2021 12:52:03 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 10" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:07:50 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="10">
				<outline text="The deed is done, 1PM Eastern" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:09:34 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;img src=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/10/10/inlineImage.png&quot;&gt;" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:09:36 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Bumped version to 2.0.9" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:16:46 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Four more things to do" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:16:52 GMT">
						<outline text="Build the Electric Drummer release." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:18:15 GMT" icon="check"/>
						<outline text="Flip the repo, make it public, and change its name to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerSupport&quot;&gt;Drummer Support&lt;/a&gt;." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:17:10 GMT" icon="check">
							<outline text="The links are not broken -- GitHub did a nice thing, they redirect from the old URLs to the new ones. " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:41:04 GMT"/>
							<outline text="Never mind." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:41:21 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="Edit the readme on the Support site." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:35:03 GMT" icon="check">
							<outline text="I'm sure there are things I missed, changing it from private to public." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:50:31 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="Post a link to drummer.scripting.com on scripting.com." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 16:17:25 GMT" icon="check"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Ideas for getting to the next level of user docs" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:08:10 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I write docs in the change notes (see below), figuring at some point I'll go through the outline and pick out things that are not in the published docs." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:08:15 GMT"/>
					<outline text="But I know I've missed a lot." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:08:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This is another kind of review we could do together, and in doing so create a new level of thoroughness in software docs." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:08:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I also think we should do the index-in-the-back-of-the-book type thing for these docs, by hand, to get the experience. " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:09:10 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Changed where Drummer redirects to" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:07:51 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I know it's confusing that when you open a second instance of Drummer (web) it redirects the previous instance, in the background, to scripting.com. At the time, I didn't have any other obvious choice of where to redirect to, and the browser won't let me close the tab (that would be the obvious choice). " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 15:07:59 GMT"/>
					<outline text="After Anton's report, I gave it some thought and decided a better place to redirect to is the new &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/about.opml&quot;&gt;About page&lt;/a&gt;. I thought about creating a special page just for this purpose but couldn't figure out how to explain it to someone who will probably have no clue they did what they did. It does this to protect you from having two versions of outlines conflicting with each other. " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 21:48:37 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There are other ways to deal with it, I've since learned, but at this stage can't do anything more complicated that what I've done here. " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 21:49:13 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The change notes outline is a blog too" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:33:21 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="BTW --" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:33:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The change notes outline is also a blog." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:33:30 GMT">
						<outline text="http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:33:36 GMT" type="link" url="http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Which you can subscribe to in your favorite RSS reader." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:33:38 GMT">
						<outline text="http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/rss.xml" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:33:36 GMT" type="link" url="http://xmlviewer.scripting.com/?url=http://scripting.com/drummer/blog/rss.xml"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The page is flipped" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 21:49:37 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Tomorrow is a new project. Not even sure which one it'll be. " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 21:49:45 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Probably still sweeping up after today's show. " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 21:50:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Feels good to have turned the corner. " created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 21:50:14 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Drummer really is a better way to blog." created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 17:40:05 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Still diggin!" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2021 21:50:29 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 9" created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 14:29:37 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="09">
				<outline text="Podcast" created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 14:29:38 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I recorded a &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/10/09/updateForDrummerUsers.m4a&quot;&gt;24 minute podcast&lt;/a&gt; about what's going on." created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 14:29:44 GMT" enclosure="http://scripting.com/2021/10/09/updateForDrummerUsers.m4a" enclosureType="audio/mpeg" enclosureLength="12474515"/>
					<outline text="It's a quiet period as I get ready to flip the switch from private to public. Taking notes on changes, but not publishing them now, rather I'll post them all here at once when it's time to open up." created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 15:24:03 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I talk about some of those changes in the podcast. " created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 14:30:45 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Still diggin! " created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 15:24:47 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;img src=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2017/09/11/mrNatural.png&quot;&gt;" created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 14:31:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: I considered how we did the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/frontier/beginning/whatFrontierIs.html&quot;&gt;online docs&lt;/a&gt; for Frontier when organizing Drummer's. " created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 14:34:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PPS: If you have a question, I started a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerTesting/issues/54&quot;&gt;thread&lt;/a&gt; in the repo for that. " created="Sat, 09 Oct 2021 14:45:49 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 7" created="Thu, 07 Oct 2021 12:22:42 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="07">
				<outline text="Sunday is the day" created="Thu, 07 Oct 2021 12:22:43 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Since Sunday is the 27th anniversary of blogging at scripting.com (or anywhere, for that matter), let's make that the day that the doors officially open for Drummer. There will still be things to do at that point, and that's ok. As they say software is a process. " created="Thu, 07 Oct 2021 12:22:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I've written about this on my blog, of course. ðŸ˜€" created="Thu, 07 Oct 2021 12:32:11 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 6" created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 15:32:19 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="06">
				<outline text="Changes in Electric Drummer (will be available when new E/D is released)" created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 16:41:34 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="When you double-click on a Twitter node, the tweet opens in an external browser window, not one inside the Electron environment. " created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 16:41:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Docs menu commands now open the docs pages in external browser windows in E/D." created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 16:44:25 GMT">
						<outline text="I changed the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/?verb=webBrowser.openUrl&quot;&gt;webBrowser.openUrl&lt;/a&gt; verb to do this in all cases. " created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 16:44:48 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Change notes archives updated" created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 15:32:20 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Archived September changes, turned the headline in the Change Notes outline to an include node. " created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 15:32:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The file went from 91K to 11.2K." created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 15:33:06 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I uploaded the Markdown versions of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerTesting/blob/main/notes/2021/08.md&quot;&gt;August&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerTesting/blob/main/notes/2021/09.md&quot;&gt;September&lt;/a&gt; to the Drummer testing repo. I find it's valuable to read them in this format too, I remember ideas I noted but haven't acted on yet. If you want to continue to help testing, you might get ideas of things to look at by reading through these files.  " created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 15:44:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I added include nodes for: February, March, April, May, June, July (all of July, not just the 31st) " created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 16:03:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Also added the OPML source files to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerTesting/tree/main/notes/2021&quot;&gt;GitHub repo&lt;/a&gt;, as part of the record. " created="Wed, 06 Oct 2021 16:36:37 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 5" created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:22:47 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="05">
				<outline text="Please keep testing and using" created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:19:11 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Please keep using Drummer and reporting problems. " created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:19:15 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Report things that fail. I'm not concerned so much about esthetic glitches or long-term problems we can work around, rather things that used to work that don't work now. This is called &quot;regression testing.&quot; Did something we do cause the product to regress?" created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:21:42 GMT"/>
					<outline text="You won't see many coding updates here until we go public with Drummer. " created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:20:01 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I am working, steadily and methodically (I hope) but not taking chances on breaking things. " created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:22:14 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I want a product that's at least as stable as LO2, which has proven to be very stable. " created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:20:42 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The time to flip the switch is soon. Please find the problems now if you can, they may be harder to deal with later. " created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:21:00 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Thanks!" created="Tue, 05 Oct 2021 15:23:53 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 3" created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 14:45:29 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="03">
				<outline text="Note to testers" created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:06 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Drummer feels stable. " created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:09 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Can we verify that?" created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="What to do to test..." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:24 GMT">
						<outline text="Hoist in one of your tabs." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:28 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Try opening another file. " created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:39 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Switch back and forth between tabs." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:49 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Did the outline you opened get overwritten? " created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:05:56 GMT">
							<outline text="This is something that used to happen." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:06:19 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="Keep the change notes outline (this list) open." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:06:27 GMT"/>
						<outline text="When it updates do other outlines get trashed?" created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:06:52 GMT">
							<outline text="This used to happen too." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:07:02 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="To really test it, don't have the change notes be the front tab. " created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:07:07 GMT">
							<outline text="Let it update in the background." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:07:21 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="Basically, really mix it up, be creative, do things you don't usually do" created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:07:33 GMT"/>
						<outline text="It'll be a PITA to find out there are big problems later. " created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:07:52 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Now is the time." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 17:08:04 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="More on keyboard customization" created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 14:45:30 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="With Scott Hanson. I just posted a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerTesting/issues/49#issuecomment-932965824&quot;&gt;summary&lt;/a&gt; of how Drummer configures the keyboard internally. It probably would be pretty straightforward to give this ability to Drummer users, esp since Drummer has a scripting capability and you can have code run at startup." created="Sun, 03 Oct 2021 14:45:39 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 2" created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 12:33:30 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="02">
				<outline text="New Electric Drummer release" created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 15:56:42 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Last E/D release was on September 23, there have been a bunch of fixes since then." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 15:56:49 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The version number displayed in the upper right corner is now meaningful, it's the same version as the web drummer, so today that number is 2.0.8." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 15:57:10 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Fixes in this release include all the hoisting fixes, keyboard commands for Find and Find Again (cmd-f and cmd-g). " created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 15:57:41 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Download from the link on the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/electricDrummer.opml&quot;&gt;Electric Drummer download&lt;/a&gt; page. " created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 16:04:40 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Radio3 change and Drummer blogs" created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 14:35:58 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Anton reported a problem with the Links page on his Drummer blog, and on the Links page on Scripting News." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 14:36:11 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I believe I have fixed the problem in both places, by making a change in Radio3. Rather than having the blogs do the rendering of the HTML for the linkblog, I have Radio3 do it. It's a better distribution of labor, and it was easier to work in Radio3 than in the blog rendering code." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 14:36:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The new version of Radio3 is 0.7.15." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 14:37:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's how to update your linkblog so the new code will find the rendered HTML." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 14:38:15 GMT">
						<outline text="Either post a link to your linkblog, or edit a link and repost it. The link doesn't have to change, it just needs to force a rebuild of all the Radio3 files which will now include the HTML rendering. If it works, say on Anton's blog, &lt;a href=&quot;http://twitter.radio3.io/users/mistersugar/linkblog.html&quot;&gt;this link&lt;/a&gt; will work. At that point, when you reload Anton's blog, its &lt;a href=&quot;http://oldschool.scripting.com/mistersugar/?tab=links&quot;&gt;links page&lt;/a&gt; will no longer be blank (as it was after I made this change)." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 14:38:40 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Let's keep a lookout on the Links page to make sure it keeps working. This is very old and strange code written mostly in 2014, when I didn't understand JS as well as I do today, so it can be a bit flaky as we just found out." created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 14:41:32 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Blogging docs page" created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 12:33:31 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I added &lt;a href=&quot;http://docserver.scripting.com/drummer/blogging.opml#1633177803000&quot;&gt;sections&lt;/a&gt; about creating Links and About pages to the Drummer blog. " created="Sat, 02 Oct 2021 12:33:38 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="October 1" created="Fri, 01 Oct 2021 14:47:16 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="01">
				<outline text="Linkblog page on Drummer blogs" created="Fri, 01 Oct 2021 14:47:17 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Anton &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerTesting/issues/35#issuecomment-931829468&quot;&gt;reports&lt;/a&gt; a problem with the linkblog page on Drummer blogs, and observes that the same problem is appearing on the Scripting News home page." created="Fri, 01 Oct 2021 14:47:29 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I verified that there is a problem there. And I got to work on moving the code that Radio3 uses to render the blog, into Scripting News, and now it works there too. I'm going to let it burn in for a bit to be sure it's working there, before porting the change into Drummer. " created="Fri, 01 Oct 2021 14:47:57 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			</outline>
